Event Store Schema Design
Question: How should events be stored in the database

to the same aggregate Option A: Expected Version `csharp await eventStore AppendAsync(streamId, events, expectedVersion: 5); // Throws if current version = 5 ` ‚úÖ Standard event sourcing pattern ‚úÖ Detects all conflicts ‚ùå Requires aggregate to track version ‚ùå Developer must handle retry logic Option B: Timestamp-Based `csharp await eventStore AppendAsync(streamId, events, ifNotModifiedSince: lastRead);
`
‚úÖ Familiar HTTP-style semantics
‚ùå Less precise than version numbers
‚ùå Clock skew issues
Option C: Automatic Retry with Conflict Resolution
`csharp
options UseOptimisticConcurrency(opt => {
    opt RetryAttempts = 3;
    opt ConflictResolver<Order>((current, attempted) => {
        // Custom merge logic
    });
});
`
‚úÖ Handles most conflicts automatically
‚úÖ Better developer experience
‚ùå Complex to implement
‚ùå Not all conflicts can be auto-resolved
Decision Needed: Start with Option A (expected version), add Option C later ---
